casebody.data:
Cincinnati Bar Association v. Sullivan.

[Cite as Cincinnati Bar Assn. v. Sullivan (1991), 59 Ohio St. 3d 157.]

(No. 90-2531 Submitted February 13, 1991 Decided May 8, 1991.) *158Charles E. Hamilton and Beth A. Myers, for relator. Sharon A. Sullivan, pro se. Per Curiam.

We have reviewed the record and agree with the board’s findings and recommendation. Accordingly, we publicly reprimand Sullivan and tax costs to her.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Re snick, JJ., concur.
